	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jan 7th 8:42 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1090 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Validous Custodus does not drop in Kael Drakkel.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can buy it in Katta Castellum or farm it there.  Frankly its not worth it.  Ry'Gor has better AC than Lambent or Fine Steel plate (except for the breastplate), has good stat buffs all around (especially STR and DEX where it counts most early in life), and has mana bonuses that will be useful later in a bards life.  Ry'Gor will last into your early 40's with no problem.  <br><br>Before you knock CHA too much - When I and my group get in trouble that ghetto mez we have, Kelin's Lucid Lullaby (now a single target mez), has saved my or my groups ass(es) more times than I care to remember.  Mez the mob just long enough to have everyone run for the hills.  In places where Selo's won't work and swarms are common (Netherbian Lair for example) that might be the only thing that saves you.<br><br>I agree AC and HP first.  STR so you can wear that plate armor without getting encumbered.  In the end a bard is a lead aggro generator (a good bard can pull aggro off a cleric).  That's why you need HP, AC and all that armor - not so you can tank - but so you can survive your own actions.  <br><br>Proc weapons are unreliable and a waste. I agree there.  Centi Shortswords are cheap these days.  With the STA boost they are really useful for many, many levels.  Centi Longswords are even better still.<br><br>My preference with regards to rings are electrum, gold, platinum or velium fire wedding rings (AC 3/4/5/6 and HP 35/45/55/65 respectively).  The velium rings on Bertoxxolous server go for about 400pp each.  The electrum for about 150pp each.  Best rings for a bard going.<br><br>Don't waste money on focus items. They don't affect bard songs at all.  Flowing Thought items will help later on with mana regen (useful since bard Meditate caps out at 1). </p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
